cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new open source platform for end-to-end speech processing, with a focus on automatic speech recognition (ASR) using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech processing, which is a subfield of sound processing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses dynamic neural network toolkits, Chainer and PyTorch, as the main deep learning engine for ASR. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing a software platform for speech processing using AI techniques. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper provides a complete setup for speech recognition and other speech processing experiments, which involves designing and implementing a system for speech processing.
